This paper deals with image processing tasks such as shadow detection and removal, which are commonly studied in the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also proposes a novel deep neural network design, which involves attention mechanisms and recurrent neural networks, indicating a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper evaluates its method on benchmark datasets, suggesting a focus on multimedia (cs.MM) and graphics (cs.GR).
